 "components": {
  "instruction": "You are given a piece of text related to banking or payment services. Your task is to classify this text into one of the following specific categories:\n\n- automatic_top_up\n- balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer\n- beneficiary_not_allowed\n- cancel_transfer\n- card_payment_fee_charged\n- card_payment_not_recognised\n- declined_cash_withdrawal\n- exchange_rate\n- exchange_via_app\n- failed_transfer\n- get_disposable_virtual_card\n- get_physical_card\n- passcode_forgotten\n- pending_top_up\n- pending_transfer\n- receiving_money\n- reverted_card_payment?\n- top_up_by_cash_or_cheque\n- top_up_reverted\n- topping_up_by_card\n- transfer_fee_charged\n- transfer_into_account\n- transfer_timing\n- verify_my_identity\n- verify_source_of_funds\n\nTo classify the text correctly:\n1. Carefully read the user's question or statement and identify its specific intent or banking action.\n2. Match the text to the most appropriate category from the list above, based strictly on the direct subject or core request of the input. \n   - For example, questions about accessing a pin number should be mapped to 'get_physical_card' (since pin number access is typically related to receiving a physical card), not 'passcode_forgotten'.\n   - If the text refers to virtual cards, use 'get_disposable_virtual_card'.\n   - If the query is about a forgotten passcode, use 'passcode_forgotten'.\n3. Do not infer broadly or choose a related but incorrect label; always select the most specific and direct label for the main subject of the text.\n4. Only output the category label—do not add explanations or additional commentary."
 },
